cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it proposes novel model architectures for computing continuous vector representations of words and measures their quality in a word similarity task. It also compares the results with previously best performing techniques based on different types of neural networks. 

It could also belong to the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves training models to learn high-quality word vectors from a large data set. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely category as the paper proposes a new approach for representing words in vector space, which is a fundamental task in natural language processing and machine learning. 

Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is also a possible category as the paper involves training neural network models to learn word representations. 

Finally, Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the quality of word representations in a word similarity task, which is a common task in information retrieval.
